message.entry: Specify table variables using a scalar subcript for data, and optionally a scalar subscript for names.
Specify data as a vector of non-negative numeric, duration, categorical or logical values.
Specify names as a string vector or a cell array of character vectors.
The "{0}" property cannot be specified when using categorical or logical data.
The length of "{0}" must match the length of "{1}".
The length of "{0}" must match the number of wedges displayed.
Specify ExplodedWedges as a logical index vector matching the length of data or a vector of subscripts to explode.
Specify ExplodedWedges as a string or cell array of character vectors that are data categories.
Labels have been reset and will be automatically generated. To use custom Labels, specify them after setting {0}.
ExplodedWedges has been reset to empty. ExplodedWedges must be specified after setting {0}.
Value must be a positive whole number or Inf.
When 'ShowOthers' is on, the name ''{0}'' is reserved.
Cannot update chart to show only zero-sized wedges. Display data is all zero.
Cannot update chart. Data contains only undefined values and 'ShowOthers' is set to 'off'.
